Program: Outlook
Title: I Blew Whistle on Army Deaths
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01cjrfp
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 1 Aug 2013
Babita Sharma talks to Justin Watt, the US soldier who blew the whistle on his fellow troops after they raped a girl and killed her and her family during the Iraq War. Pakistani student Khan Muhammad Qureshi describes his mission - to save the trees in his home district of Diamer in the north of the country. Shawnee Baughmann the student who donned a virtual reality helmet to find out how it feels to be a cow! Plus, British playwright Alan Bennett. Show less